---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Shipwright Harness — Autonomous Delivery Agent for Claude Code | App Vitals"
  description="Shipwright Harness is a free, MIT-licensed autonomous delivery agent for Claude Code — runs on your infrastructure, ships production PRs, created by App Vitals."
  keywords="autonomous coding agent, open source, Claude Code, AI engineering, Shipwright, App Vitals, MIT, claude code, claude code plugin, claude code pipeline, autonomous delivery agent"
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="glow-orb w-[500px] h-[500px] bg-electric-500/[0.07] top-[-10%] right-[-5%] animate-glow-drift" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="glow-orb w-[400px] h-[400px] bg-accent-violet/[0.05] bottom-[0%] left-[-10%] animate-glow-drift-slow" aria-hidden="true"></div>

    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 pt-24 pb-20 md:pt-32 md:pb-24 relative z-10">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3 mb-6 opacity-0 animate-fade-in-up">
          <span class="font-mono text-[13px] text-electric-400 tracking-[0.25em] uppercase">Open Source · MIT · Built by App Vitals</span>
          <a href="https://github.com/app-vitals/shipwright" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1 rounded-full border border-white/[0.1] bg-white/[0.04] text-[12px] text-white/60 font-mono hover:border-white/20 transition-colors">
            <svg class="w-3.5 h-3.5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M12 .297c-6.63 0-12 5.373-12 12 0 5.303 3.438 9.8 8.205 11.385.6.113.82-.258.82-.577 0-.285-.01-1.04-.015-2.04-3.338.724-4.042-1.61-4.042-1.61C4.422 18.07 3.633 17.7 3.633 17.7c-1.087-.744.084-.729.084-.729 1.205.084 1.838 1.236 1.838 1.236 1.07 1.835 2.809 1.305 3.495.998.108-.776.417-1.305.76-1.605-2.665-.3-5.466-1.332-5.466-5.93 0-1.31.465-2.38 1.235-3.22-.135-.303-.54-1.523.105-3.176 0 0 1.005-.322 3.3 1.23.96-.267 1.98-.399 3-.405 1.02.006 2.04.138 3 .405 2.28-1.552 3.285-1.23 3.285-1.23.645 1.653.24 2.873.12 3.176.765.84 1.23 1.91 1.23 3.22 0 4.61-2.805 5.625-5.475 5.92.42.36.81 1.096.81 2.22 0 1.606-.015 2.896-.015 3.286 0 .315.21.69.825.57C20.565 22.092 24 17.592 24 12.297c0-6.627-5.373-12-12-12"/></svg>
            github.com/app-vitals/shipwright
          </a>
        </div>
        <h1 class="font-display text-[clamp(2.5rem,5vw,4.5rem)] font-bold leading-[1.05] tracking-[-0.03em] opacity-0 animate-fade-in-up-delay-1">
          The own-it alternative<br />
          <span class="gradient-text">to closed AI agents.</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="mt-8 text-[18px] text-white/50 max-w-xl leading-[1.7] opacity-0 animate-fade-in-up-delay-2">
          Shipwright is a free, MIT-licensed autonomous coding agent built on Claude Code. It runs on your infrastructure, on your codebase — your code never leaves your control. Created and maintained by App Vitals.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-10 flex flex-col gap-4 opacity-0 animate-fade-in-up-delay-3 sm:flex-row sm:items-center sm:gap-3">
          <a
            href="https://cal.com/app-vitals/discovery"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-10 py-4 bg-white text-navy-950 rounded-full text-[16px] font-semibold tracking-wide transition-all duration-300 hover:shadow-[0_0_60px_rgba(59,130,246,0.3)] hover:scale-[1.02]"
          >
            Book a Discovery Call
            <svg class="ml-2 w-4 h-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M13.5 4.5L21 12m0 0l-7.5 7.5M21 12H3" />
            </svg>
          </a>
          <a
            href="https://shipwrightharness.com"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-8 py-4 rounded-full border border-white/[0.12] bg-white/[0.04] text-[14px] text-white/70 font-mono tracking-wider transition-all duration-300 hover:border-white/25 hover:text-white"
          >
            /plugin install shipwright@app-vitals/shipwright
          </a>
        </div>
        <p class="mt-4 text-[13px] text-white/40 opacity-0 animate-fade-in-up-delay-3" style="animation-delay: 0.6s">Free · MIT Licensed</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Built and maintained by App Vitals -->
  <section class="relative">
    <div class="gradient-divider"></div>
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-24 md:py-32">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[1fr,1.5fr] gap-16 items-start">
        <div class="reveal">
          <p class="font-mono text-[12px] text-electric-400 uppercase tracking-[0.3em] mb-4">Created by App Vitals</p>
          <h2 class="font-display text-[clamp(1.5rem,3vw,2.25rem)] font-bold tracking-[-0.02em] leading-[1.2]">
            We build it.<br />
            <span class="text-white/40">We ship with it daily.</span>
          </h2>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-6 text-[16px] text-white/45 leading-[1.8] reveal" style="transition-delay: 150ms;">
          <p>
            Shipwright was created by Dan McAulay and Dave O'Dell — the co-founders of App Vitals. It's the autonomous coding system we use to ship production work across our own engagements. We didn't build a demo — we built the pipeline we trust with real codebases, every day.
          </p>
          <p>
            We open sourced it because we believe that when an AI agent has write access to your codebase, you should own the system. Not rent it. Shipwright is MIT licensed, self-hosted, and free — and App Vitals is the team maintaining it and pushing it forward.
          </p>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 pt-2">
            <span class="px-3 py-1.5 rounded-full border border-electric-500/20 bg-electric-500/[0.05] text-[13px] text-electric-400 font-mono">MIT License</span>
            <span class="px-3 py-1.5 rounded-full border border-white/[0.08] bg-white/[0.03] text-[13px] text-white/60 font-mono">Self-hosted</span>
            <span class="px-3 py-1.5 rounded-full border border-white/[0.08] bg-white/[0.03] text-[13px] text-white/60 font-mono">Claude Code native</span>
            <span class="px-3 py-1.5 rounded-full border border-white/[0.08] bg-white/[0.03] text-[13px] text-white/60 font-mono">No lock-in</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="gradient-divider"></div>
  </section>

  <!-- What it does -->
  <section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-24 md:py-32">
    <div class="mb-20 reveal">
      <p class="font-mono text-[12px] text-electric-400 uppercase tracking-[0.3em] mb-4">How it works</p>
      <h2 class="font-display text-[clamp(1.75rem,4vw,3rem)] font-bold tracking-[-0.02em] max-w-2xl leading-[1.15]">
        One command.<br />
        <span class="text-white/40">Plan → Build → Review → Ship.</span>
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-6 text-[17px] text-white/40 max-w-xl leading-[1.7]">
        Shipwright turns a task in your queue into a tested, reviewed, CI-green PR — autonomously. Two modes, same engine.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 max-w-4xl">
      <div class="p-8 rounded-2xl border border-electric-500/20 bg-electric-500/[0.03] reveal">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
          <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-lg bg-electric-500/10 flex items-center justify-center">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-electric-400" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M6.75 7.5l3 2.25-3 2.25m4.5 0h3m-9 8.25h13.5A2.25 2.25 0 0021 18V6a2.25 2.25 0 00-2.25-2.25H5.25A2.25 2.25 0 003 6v12a2.25 2.25 0 002.25 2.25z" />
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-display text-[18px] font-semibold tracking-tight">Plugin Mode</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="font-mono text-[12px] text-white/30 mb-4">Inside Claude Code</p>
        <p class="text-[14px] text-white/40 leading-[1.7] mb-4">
          Install the plugin, run <code class="text-electric-400 bg-electric-500/10 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[13px]">/shipwright:dev-task</code>, and watch it pick the next ready task, write tests first, implement the feature, and open a reviewed, green PR. You stay in the loop where it matters.
        </p>
        <code class="block text-[12px] text-white/40 font-mono bg-white/[0.03] border border-white/[0.06] rounded-lg px-4 py-3">/plugin install shipwright@app-vitals/shipwright</code>
      </div>

      <div class="p-8 rounded-2xl border border-white/[0.06] bg-white/[0.02] reveal" style="transition-delay: 100ms;">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
          <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-lg bg-accent-violet/10 flex items-center justify-center">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-accent-violet" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 6v6h4.5m4.5 0a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-display text-[18px] font-semibold tracking-tight">Cloud Agent Mode</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="font-mono text-[12px] text-white/30 mb-4">Deploy to Docker / Kubernetes / GitHub Actions</p>
        <p class="text-[14px] text-white/40 leading-[1.7]">
          Deploy the agent to your cloud. DM it in Slack. @mention it in a thread. Drop a voice note. It picks the next ready task, ships the PR, and forwards metrics to your dashboard — while you sleep. 10 cron jobs out of the box.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Why open source -->
  <section class="relative">
    <div class="gradient-divider"></div>
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-24 md:py-32">
      <div class="mb-20 reveal">
        <p class="font-mono text-[12px] text-electric-400 uppercase tracking-[0.3em] mb-4">Why open source</p>
        <h2 class="font-display text-[clamp(1.75rem,4vw,3rem)] font-bold tracking-[-0.02em] max-w-2xl leading-[1.15]">
          Not renting you an AI engineer.<br />
          <span class="text-white/40">Giving you one.</span>
        </h2>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        <div class="card-glow p-8 rounded-2xl border border-white/[0.06] bg-white/[0.02] hover:border-white/[0.12] transition-all duration-500 reveal">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-xl bg-electric-500/10 flex items-center justify-center mb-6">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-electric-400" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 12.75L11.25 15 15 9.75m-3-7.036A11.959 11.959 0 013.598 6 11.99 11.99 0 003 9.749c0 5.592 3.824 10.29 9 11.623 5.176-1.332 9-6.03 9-11.622 0-1.31-.21-2.571-.598-3.751h-.152c-3.196 0-6.1-1.248-8.25-3.285z" />
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-display text-[20px] font-semibold mb-3 tracking-tight">Your code, your control</h3>
          <p class="text-[15px] text-white/40 leading-[1.7]">
            The managed-agent market is full of "trust us" SaaS. Your code goes to their servers, priced at their rates, on their terms. Shipwright runs in your environment. MIT licensed. Fork it. Own it. No lock-in.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="card-glow p-8 rounded-2xl border border-white/[0.06] bg-white/[0.02] hover:border-white/[0.12] transition-all duration-500 reveal" style="transition-delay: 100ms;">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-xl bg-accent-cyan/10 flex items-center justify-center mb-6">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-accent-cyan" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 12.75L11.25 15 15 9.75M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-display text-[20px] font-semibold mb-3 tracking-tight">Same bar as human code</h3>
          <p class="text-[15px] text-white/40 leading-[1.7]">
            Tests land with the code, every time. CI must be green before merge. No exceptions. Shipwright is built to the same review and quality standards your engineers already use — because we use it on real production codebases.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="card-glow p-8 rounded-2xl border border-white/[0.06] bg-white/[0.02] hover:border-white/[0.12] transition-all duration-500 reveal" style="transition-delay: 200ms;">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-xl bg-accent-violet/10 flex items-center justify-center mb-6">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-accent-violet" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M3 13.125C3 12.504 3.504 12 4.125 12h2.25c.621 0 1.125.504 1.125 1.125v6.75C7.5 20.496 6.996 21 6.375 21h-2.25A1.125 1.125 0 013 19.875v-6.75zM9.75 8.625c0-.621.504-1.125 1.125-1.125h2.25c.621 0 1.125.504 1.125 1.125v11.25c0 .621-.504 1.125-1.125 1.125h-2.25a1.125 1.125 0 01-1.125-1.125V8.625zM16.5 4.125c0-.621.504-1.125 1.125-1.125h2.25C20.496 3 21 3.504 21 4.125v15.75c0 .621-.504 1.125-1.125 1.125h-2.25a1.125 1.125 0 01-1.125-1.125V4.125z" />
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-display text-[20px] font-semibold mb-3 tracking-tight">Metrics on your pipeline</h3>
          <p class="text-[15px] text-white/40 leading-[1.7]">
            First-time-quality rate. Estimation accuracy. Review-verdict trends. Cycle time. Your data, running locally on SQLite or against your own PostHog. No external dashboards, no vendor accounts.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="gradient-divider"></div>
  </section>

  <!-- Quickstart -->
  <section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-24 md:py-32">
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[1fr,1.5fr] gap-16 items-start">
      <div class="reveal">
        <p class="font-mono text-[12px] text-electric-400 uppercase tracking-[0.3em] mb-4">Quickstart</p>
        <h2 class="font-display text-[clamp(1.5rem,3vw,2.25rem)] font-bold tracking-[-0.02em] leading-[1.2]">
          5 minutes.<br />
          <span class="text-white/40">No accounts. No secrets.</span>
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-6 text-[16px] text-white/40 leading-[1.7]">
          A few copy-paste commands spin up the metrics dashboard locally. Offline by default.
        </p>
        <a
          href="https://shipwrightharness.com"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="inline-flex items-center mt-8 text-[15px] text-electric-400 hover:text-electric-300 transition-colors font-mono"
        >
          Full docs at shipwrightharness.com →
        </a>
      </div>
      <div class="reveal font-mono text-[13px] bg-white/[0.02] border border-white/[0.06] rounded-2xl p-8 space-y-3" style="transition-delay: 150ms;">
        <p class="text-white/25 text-[11px] uppercase tracking-[0.2em] mb-4">Run in your terminal</p>
        <p class="text-white/60 leading-[1.7]">Set up Shipwright Harness locally and open the metrics dashboard.</p>
        <p class="text-white/30">1. In a terminal, run:</p>
        <code class="block text-electric-400 pl-4 leading-[1.8]">git clone https://github.com/app-vitals/shipwright.git<br />&amp;&amp; cd shipwright &amp;&amp; ./scripts/quickstart.sh</code>
        <p class="text-white/30 pt-2">2. Install the plugin:</p>
        <code class="block text-electric-400 pl-4">/plugin install shipwright@app-vitals/shipwright</code>
        <p class="text-white/30 pt-2">3. Open the dashboard:</p>
        <code class="block text-electric-400 pl-4">http://localhost:3460/dashboard</code>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Design Partner program -->
  <section class="relative">
    <div class="gradient-divider"></div>
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-24 md:py-32">
      <div class="mb-16 reveal">
        <p class="font-mono text-[12px] text-electric-400 uppercase tracking-[0.3em] mb-4">Want us to install it for you? · Design Partners</p>
        <h2 class="font-display text-[clamp(1.75rem,4vw,3rem)] font-bold tracking-[-0.02em] max-w-2xl leading-[1.15]">
          Dan and Dave.<br />
          <span class="text-white/40">In your environment. End to end.</span>
        </h2>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[1.2fr,1fr] gap-12 items-start max-w-5xl">
        <div class="space-y-6 text-[16px] text-white/45 leading-[1.8] reveal">
          <p>
            Shipwright is free and open source — install it yourself anytime. But if your engineering org wants the founders of Shipwright to install it, configure it to your codebase, and run alongside your team through the first 8–10 weeks, that's our Design Partner program.
          </p>
          <p>
            Design partners get a <span class="text-white/70">reduced-rate pilot</span>, weekly working sessions with Dan and Dave, and direct influence on the roadmap. In exchange, we ask for real engagement, honest feedback, and permission to share results — even when we anonymize the specifics.
          </p>
          <p>
            We're taking a small cohort. If you want autonomous programming installed and running by the people who built it, we'd like to talk.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="p-8 rounded-2xl border border-electric-500/20 bg-electric-500/[0.03] reveal" style="transition-delay: 150ms;">
          <p class="font-mono text-[12px] text-electric-400 uppercase tracking-[0.2em] mb-6">What a pilot looks like</p>
          <ul class="space-y-4">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-electric-400 mt-0.5">—</span>
              <span class="text-[14px] text-white/55 leading-[1.6]">8–10 weeks, install to hand-off</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-electric-400 mt-0.5">—</span>
              <span class="text-[14px] text-white/55 leading-[1.6]">Weekly working sessions with Dan and Dave</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-electric-400 mt-0.5">—</span>
              <span class="text-[14px] text-white/55 leading-[1.6]">Reduced-rate pilot pricing, shaped to scope</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-electric-400 mt-0.5">—</span>
              <span class="text-[14px] text-white/55 leading-[1.6]">Direct influence on the Shipwright roadmap</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="gradient-divider"></div>
  </section>

  <!-- Final CTA — two paths -->
  <section class="relative py-24 md:py-32">
    <div class="glow-orb w-[600px] h-[400px] bg-electric-500/[0.05] top-1/2 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 animate-glow-drift" aria-hidden="true"></div>

    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 relative z-10">
      <div class="text-center mb-16 reveal">
        <h2 class="font-display text-[clamp(1.75rem,4vw,3rem)] font-bold tracking-[-0.02em] leading-[1.15]">
          Two ways to get started.
        </h2>
      </div>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <div class="p-8 rounded-2xl border border-white/[0.08] bg-white/[0.02] text-center reveal">
          <p class="font-mono text-[12px] text-electric-400 uppercase tracking-[0.2em] mb-4">Free · Open Source</p>
          <h3 class="font-display text-[22px] font-bold mb-4">Install it yourself</h3>
          <p class="text-[15px] text-white/40 leading-[1.7] mb-8">
            MIT licensed. Clone the repo, run the quickstart, have the metrics dashboard up in 5 minutes. No accounts required.
          </p>
          <a
            href="https://shipwrightharness.com"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-full px-8 py-4 bg-white text-navy-950 rounded-full text-[15px] font-semibold tracking-wide transition-all duration-300 hover:shadow-[0_0_60px_rgba(59,130,246,0.3)] hover:scale-[1.02]"
          >
            Get Started Free →
          </a>
          <a
            href="https://github.com/app-vitals/shipwright"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-full mt-3 px-8 py-3 rounded-full border border-white/[0.10] text-[14px] text-white/50 font-mono transition-all hover:border-white/20 hover:text-white/70"
          >
            ⭐ Star on GitHub
          </a>
        </div>

        <div class="p-8 rounded-2xl border border-electric-500/20 bg-electric-500/[0.03] text-center reveal" style="transition-delay: 100ms;">
          <p class="font-mono text-[12px] text-electric-400 uppercase tracking-[0.2em] mb-4">Design Partner · App Vitals</p>
          <h3 class="font-display text-[22px] font-bold mb-4">Have us install it</h3>
          <p class="text-[15px] text-white/40 leading-[1.7] mb-8">
            Dan and Dave handle the install, configuration, and first 8–10 weeks alongside your team. Limited cohort.
          </p>
          <a
            href="https://cal.com/team/app-vitals"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-full px-8 py-4 rounded-full border border-electric-500/40 bg-electric-500/10 text-electric-300 text-[15px] font-semibold tracking-wide transition-all duration-300 hover:bg-electric-500/20 hover:border-electric-500/60"
          >
            Book a Discovery Call →
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
